    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The small-world coefficient is defined as: sigma = C/Cr / L/Lr where C and L are respectively the average clustering coefficient and average shortest path length of G. Cr and Lr are respectively the average clustering coefficient and average shortest path length of an equivalent random graph."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "A graph is commonly classified as small-world if sigma>1."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 0,
      "target": null,
      "title": null,
      "type": "Section"
    },
